# Build context for the app image is the repo root (compose: `context: ..`), so without this
# file every `docker build` streams ~9.5 GB to the daemon before a line compiles. The root
# Dockerfile only ever reads frontend/ and backend/src + backend/Cargo.*; everything below is
# either huge, regenerated inside the image, or irrelevant to it.
#
# Denylist rather than allowlist on purpose: a new top-level file the Dockerfile needs should
# just work, and the entries here are the ones that actually carry weight.

# Chain data and dumps — the 9.2 GB that dominates the context.
snapshots/
backups/
*.dat
*.tar.gz

# Host-side build output. node_modules is reinstalled by `npm ci` and target by `cargo build`
# inside their build stages; copying the host's would also poison the cache with foreign artifacts.
**/node_modules/
backend/target/
frontend/dist/

# Node data volumes, if a bind-mounted run ever leaves them in the tree.
core-data/
knots-data/
tor-data/
app-db/

# Nothing in the build reads these.
.git/
.gitignore
.dockerignore
docs/
e2e/
scripts/
compose/
nodes/
miner/
mdns/
tor/
*.md
LICENSE
*.log
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/

# Secrets must never reach a build layer, even unreferenced.
.env
**/.env
**/*.env
